author: Jenny Hsu
title: Oil Prices Steady in Asian Trade
text: 0122 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude oil prices are barely moving in early Asian trade Friday as the news of falling U.S. crude supplies is offset by Federal Reserve Chairwoman Janet Yellen’s latest comments that “it will likely be appropriate to raise the target range of the federal-fund rate sometimes later this year.” On Thursday, data provider Genscape Inc. said crude supplies in Cushing fell by more than 500,000 barrels in the week ended Tuesday. “Yellen’s comments will send jitters across the market and players will remain in a risk-averse mode for the rest of the day,” says Barnabas Gan, an OCBC analyst who says prices...
